<br>
mgb - great aa for the raiding shaman. i got this right after canni 5. very usefull.<br>
<br>
virulent paralysis - i just got this. fun aa, and seems to be very usefull also. great for positioning mobs or pulling them out of walls and stuff. think i might go for lvl 3 of this one pretty soon. only problem i have found with it is the duration doesnt seem to be what thay say it is most of the time, and i have gotten a more resists then i expected in last few days since i have had it.<br>
<br>
radiant cure - never thought i would use this as much as i do. i have lvl 2 and this has come in very handy many times. i guess theres more caster mobs out there then i realized lol. cheap aa and worth it even for the solo/ grouping shaman as well as the raiding shaman .<br>
<br>
quick buff - i think this one is underated. especialy for for the raiding and solo shaman. i only have lvl 1 atm but if your in the heat of battle on a raid with people asking for buffs, or soloing and want to get that torpor or Q off faster this does come in handy. i havnt regreted droping a the 3 aa's to get lvl 1. its not priority to get this higher atm but im sure ill at least get lvl 2 sooner or later<br>
<br>
run speed - i wasnt gonna bother getting into the general aa's but this one is a must IMO, even for us classes that have sow. alot of the best places seem to be indoors. and what better way to unlock archtype then to be able to run faster indoors.<br>
